---
layout: layout-base.njk
pagination:
  data: cropCitySummaries
  size: 1
  alias: pageData
permalink: "{{ pageData.url }}index.html"
eleventyComputed:
  title: "When to Plant {{ pageData.cropName }} in {{ pageData.cityName }}, {{ pageData.regionName }} | GrowByDate"
  description: "{{ pageData.cropName }} planting timing, frost dates, and maturity outlook for {{ pageData.cityName }}, {{ pageData.regionName }}."
  canonical: "https://growbydate.com{{ pageData.url }}"
---

{% macro formatMmdd(mmdd) %}
  {% if not mmdd %}
    —
  {% else %}
    {{ mmdd
      | replace("01-", "Jan ")
      | replace("02-", "Feb ")
      | replace("03-", "Mar ")
      | replace("04-", "Apr ")
      | replace("05-", "May ")
      | replace("06-", "Jun ")
      | replace("07-", "Jul ")
      | replace("08-", "Aug ")
      | replace("09-", "Sep ")
      | replace("10-", "Oct ")
      | replace("11-", "Nov ")
      | replace("12-", "Dec ")
      | replace("-0", " ")
      | replace("-", " ")
    }}
  {% endif %}
{% endmacro %}

{% macro mmddToDayOfYear(mmdd) %}
  {% if not mmdd %}
    {{ "" }}
  {% else %}
    {% set parts = mmdd.split("-") %}
    {% set month = parts[0] | int %}
    {% set day = parts[1] | int %}
    {% set monthStarts = [0, 31, 59, 90, 120, 151, 181, 212, 243, 273, 304, 334] %}
    {{ monthStarts[month - 1] + day }}
  {% endif %}
{% endmacro %}

{% set cropPlural = pageData.cropName %}
{% set cropLower = pageData.cropName | lower %}
{% set cropSingular = pageData.cropSingularName or pageData.cropName %}
{% set cropSingularLower = cropSingular | lower %}
{% set outlookClass = pageData.fit.confidence %}

{% set plantingLabel = "Typical planting date" %}
{% if pageData.planting.plantOutDate %}
  {% set plantingLabel = "Typical transplant date" %}
{% elif pageData.planting.directSowDate %}
  {% set plantingLabel = "Typical sowing date" %}
{% endif %}

{% set plantingDoy = (mmddToDayOfYear(pageData.planting.primaryPlantingDate) | trim) %}
{% set fallDoy = (mmddToDayOfYear(pageData.frost.fall50) | trim) %}
{% set outdoorRunway = null %}
{% if plantingDoy and fallDoy %}
  {% set outdoorRunway = (fallDoy | int) - (plantingDoy | int) %}
{% endif %}

<header class="header cropHero">
  <p class="eyebrow">Climate-based {{ cropSingularLower }} planting guide for {{ pageData.cityName }}, {{ pageData.regionName }}</p>
  <h1>When to Plant {{ cropPlural }} in {{ pageData.cityName }}</h1>
  <p class="lede">{{ pageData.lede }}</p>
</header>

<section class="quickAnswer card" aria-label="Quick answer">
  <div class="quickAnswerTop">
    <h2>Quick answer</h2>

    <div class="fitBadge fitBadge-{{ outlookClass }}">
      {% if pageData.fit.confidence == "strong" %}
        Strong fit
      {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "good" %}
        Good fit
      {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "borderline" %}
        Borderline
      {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "risky" %}
        Risky fit
      {% else %}
        {{ pageData.fit.confidence | capitalize }}
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="muted">
    Here is the typical planting and maturity outlook for {{ cropLower }} in {{ pageData.cityName }}.
  </p>

  <div class="quickStats">
    {% if pageData.planting.primaryPlantingDate %}
      <div class="statCard">
        <span class="statLabel">{{ plantingLabel }}</span>
        <strong>{{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.primaryPlantingDate) }}</strong>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="statCard">
<span class="statLabel">Available GDD (base {{ pageData.crop.gddBase or 50 }})</span>
      <strong>{{ pageData.fit.availableGddFromPlanting }}</strong>
    </div>

    <div class="statCard">
      <span class="statLabel">Typical crop GDD target</span>
      <strong>{{ pageData.crop.gddTargetTypical }}</strong>
    </div>

    {% if pageData.fit.gddMargin != null %}
      <div class="statCard">
        <span class="statLabel">Heat margin</span>
        <strong>{% if pageData.fit.gddMargin > 0 %}+{% endif %}{{ pageData.fit.gddMargin }}</strong>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="statCard">
      <span class="statLabel">Typical last spring frost</span>
      <strong>{{ formatMmdd(pageData.frost.spring50) }}</strong>
    </div>

    <div class="statCard">
      <span class="statLabel">Typical first fall frost</span>
      <strong>{{ formatMmdd(pageData.frost.fall50) }}</strong>
    </div>

    <div class="statCard">
      <span class="statLabel">Typical frost-free days</span>
      <strong>{{ pageData.frost.frostFreeDays }}</strong>
    </div>

{% if outdoorRunway != null %}
  <div class="statCard">
    <span class="statLabel">Outdoor growing runway</span>
    <strong>{{ outdoorRunway }} days</strong>
  </div>
{% endif %}
</div>

  <div class="quickSummary">
    {% if pageData.fit.confidence == "strong" %}
      <p>
        {{ cropPlural }} are usually a strong fit for {{ pageData.cityName }}. In a typical year, most gardeners have enough seasonal heat and enough runway for reliable results.
      </p>
    {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "good" %}
      <p>
        {{ cropPlural }} generally perform well in {{ pageData.cityName }}. Planting on time and choosing climate-appropriate varieties still matter, but the overall fit is favorable.
      </p>
    {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "borderline" %}
      <p>
        {{ cropPlural }} can work in {{ pageData.cityName }}, but the margin is tighter. Earlier varieties, warm sites, and timely planting make a noticeable difference.
      </p>
    {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "risky" %}
      <p>
        {{ cropPlural }} are a risky crop in {{ pageData.cityName }}. Success usually depends on the fastest varieties and the warmest, most protected planting conditions.
      </p>
    {% endif %}

    <p>
      {{ pageData.cityName }} usually sees a last spring frost around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.frost.spring50) }} and a first fall frost around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.frost.fall50) }}, creating a typical frost-free window of about {{ pageData.frost.frostFreeDays }} days.
    </p>

    {% if pageData.fit.gddMargin != null %}
      {% if pageData.fit.gddMargin >= 150 %}
        <p>
          From the usual planting window, {{ pageData.cityName }} typically provides about {{ pageData.fit.availableGddFromPlanting }} growing degree days for {{ cropLower }}. With a typical crop target of {{ pageData.crop.gddTargetTypical }}, that leaves a heat margin of +{{ pageData.fit.gddMargin }}. That means the season usually provides enough accumulated warmth for {{ cropLower }} to mature reliably, not just to fit the calendar on paper, but to actually mature in typical local conditions.
        </p>
      {% elif pageData.fit.gddMargin >= 40 %}
        <p>
          From the usual planting window, {{ pageData.cityName }} typically provides about {{ pageData.fit.availableGddFromPlanting }} growing degree days for {{ cropLower }}. With a typical crop target of {{ pageData.crop.gddTargetTypical }}, that leaves a heat margin of +{{ pageData.fit.gddMargin }}. That usually gives {{ cropLower }} enough heat to finish, but not with much room for delay, slower varieties, or cooler-than-average conditions.
        </p>
      {% elif pageData.fit.gddMargin >= 0 %}
        <p>
          From the usual planting window, {{ pageData.cityName }} typically provides about {{ pageData.fit.availableGddFromPlanting }} growing degree days for {{ cropLower }}. With a typical crop target of {{ pageData.crop.gddTargetTypical }}, the heat margin is only +{{ pageData.fit.gddMargin }}. In practice, that is a very slim buffer, so variety speed, planting timing, and site warmth matter a great deal.
        </p>
      {% else %}
        <p>
          From the usual planting window, {{ pageData.cityName }} typically provides about {{ pageData.fit.availableGddFromPlanting }} growing degree days for {{ cropLower }}, against a typical crop target of {{ pageData.crop.gddTargetTypical }}. That leaves a heat margin of {{ pageData.fit.gddMargin }}, which means the season usually falls short of the warmth this crop prefers. In practice, success depends on very fast varieties, warm sites, and consistently favorable conditions.
        </p>
      {% endif %}
    {% endif %}

  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Growing {{ cropPlural }} Successfully in {{ pageData.cityName }}</h2>

  {% if pageData.advisory %}
    <p>{{ pageData.advisory.succeed }}</p>
    <p>{{ pageData.advisory.fail }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% include "region/modules/simple-city-crop-planting-window.njk" %}

  {% if pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate and pageData.planting.plantOutDate %}
    <p>
      Gardeners usually start indoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate) }} and plant outdoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.plantOutDate) }}.
    </p>
  {% elif pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate and pageData.planting.directSowDate %}
    <p>
      Gardeners usually start indoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate) }} and sow outdoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.directSowDate) }}.
    </p>
  {% elif pageData.planting.plantOutDate %}
    <p>
      Gardeners usually plant outdoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.plantOutDate) }}.
    </p>
  {% elif pageData.planting.directSowDate %}
    <p>
      Gardeners usually sow outdoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.directSowDate) }}.
    </p>
  {% elif pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate %}
    <p>
      Gardeners usually start indoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate) }}.
    </p>
  {% endif %}

  <h3>Best {{ cropPlural }} for {{ pageData.cityName }} conditions</h3>

  {% if pageData.fit.bestVarietyParagraph %}
    <p>{{ pageData.fit.bestVarietyParagraph }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.fit.varietyClassFits and pageData.fit.varietyClassFits.length %}
    <div class="tableWrap" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <table class="table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Variety class</th>
            <th>Typical GDD need</th>
            <th>Local fit</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for v in pageData.fit.varietyClassFits %}
            <tr>
              <td>{{ v.label }}</td>
              <td>{{ v.gddTarget }}</td>
              <td>
                {% if v.fitLabel == "good" %}
                  Good fit
                {% elif v.fitLabel == "workable" %}
                  Workable
                {% elif v.fitLabel == "tight" %}
                  Tight
                {% elif v.fitLabel == "poor" %}
                  Poor fit
                {% else %}
                  —
                {% endif %}
              </td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.fit.protectionSentence %}
    <p class="small">{{ pageData.fit.protectionSentence }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.fit.fittingVarietyExamplesDetailed and pageData.fit.fittingVarietyExamplesDetailed.length %}
    <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
      Well-adapted varieties often include:
    </p>

    <ul style="margin-top:0.45rem;">
      {% for v in pageData.fit.fittingVarietyExamplesDetailed %}
        <li><strong>{{ v.name }}</strong> — {{ v.note }}</li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.fit.mainRiskSentence %}
    <p class="small muted">
      Main risk: {{ pageData.fit.mainRiskSentence }}
    </p>
  {% endif %}

  <h4>What local garden sites change for {{ cropPlural }}</h4>

  {% if pageData.advisory %}
    <p>{{ pageData.advisory.micro }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.advisory and pageData.advisory.localInterpretation %}
    <p class="small">
      {{ pageData.advisory.localInterpretation }}
    </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{% include "crop-city/modules/related-crops.njk" %}

<p class="small muted" style="margin-top:1rem;">
  For a broader local overview, see the
  <a href="/planting-dates/{% if pageData.country == 'canada' %}canada/{% endif %}{{ pageData.regionKey }}/{{ pageData.cityKey }}/">
    {{ pageData.cityName }} planting guide
  </a>.
  You can also use the <a href="/tools/growing-degree-day-planner/">Growing Degree Day Planner</a> to test planting dates and crop timing.
</p>